# Line-ending policy: store and check out LF everywhere.
# CI runs on Linux and the repo ships shell scripts (require LF), so LF is the
# single source of truth on every platform. This overrides Windows
# `core.autocrlf=true` per-file and eliminates the CRLF churn that made tracked
# files show as "modified" with no real content change.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Belt-and-suspenders: never EOL-convert or diff these as text if ever added
# (on-chain ELF dumps, account-state blobs, images, archives, wasm).
*.so   binary
*.bin  binary
*.png  binary
*.gz   binary
*.zip  binary
*.wasm binary
